articles.title: About this site
articles.description: Some additional details about the website
articles.contents:
About Me
My name is Henry
Sippel. I just graduated from high school in May and plan
on attending University of Utah in the fall. I enjoy skiing, sailing and
listening to music in my free time.
About the Project
My project, Looking at Fish Stocking data in Lake Michigan
aims to look at the different fish stocked in Lake Michigan, and the
trends of the population of fish stocked. I sourced my data from an
excel spreadsheet, which I then downloaded through RStudio and then made
my graph and website.
Goals
Visualize the number of fish stocked into the lake over time
Look at the change in fish stocking throughout different
species
Determine if there is a connection between fish stocking and years
passed
“This is Data Science” ~Preceptor
Kane’s Free High School
Data Science Bootcamp
